40|$|This essay {{argues that}} Eudora Welty’s vision was {{influenced}} by the American Gothic tradition, with its emphasis on doubleness and mystery. Indeed, not only in several interviews conceded throughout her career but also <b>in</b> <b>her</b> <b>essays</b> and <b>in</b> <b>her</b> fictional writing, did Welty refuse to indulge into conclusive generalizations or to moralize her readers. Thus, she revealed an extraordinary capacity to probe the constitutive ambivalence of situations and characters, and to allude to the flux at the heart of life. Fundação para a Ciência e a Tecnologi...|$|R
